In general, after the virus invades the host cell, the virus is first recognized by the host immune system through pattern recognition receptors (PRRs) including C-type cell receptor, Toll-like receptors (TLR), NOD-like receptor (NLR), and RIG-I-like receptor (RLR).
Through different pathways, the virus induces the emergence of inflammatory factors, dendritic cells and synthesis of type IFNs, limiting the spread of the virus and accelerates the phagocytosis of the virus.
