If the animal harbours a closely related virus that has high homology to the level of nucleotide sequence, the animal serves as the evolutionary host of HCoV.
The ancestral virus is usually well adapted to the host and is not a disease for it.
Likewise, a reservoir host, one unregulated, long-term and long-term reservoir of HCoVs.
