In contrast, if HCoV has its intermediate host prior to infecting humans, or about the same time, it is not well adapted to the new host and is often pathogenic.
This intermediate host can serve as the zoonotic reservoir of human infection, and increase the level of infection in humans as a amplifying host by allowing the virus to replicate transiently and then transmitting it to humans.
